
[1]spoliation

   SPOLIATION, n.

   1. The act of plundering, particularly of plundering an enemy in time
   of war.

   2. The act or practice of plundering neutrals at sea under authority.

   3. In ecclesiastical affairs, the act of an incumbent in taking the
   fruits of his benefice without right, but under a pretended title.
